      "author_association" : "MEMBER",
      "body" : "NACK. A bool has two states, and the confusion around this is based on a misinterpretation of at least three states (tx can be replaced \"by itself\", tx can be replaced \"via parent\", tx can't be bip125 replaced). Toggling the bool doesn't help anything in fixing the underlying misunderstanding. If you really want to fix this you may offer the consumer a way to determine the state. I think it should be sufficient to just return the two boolean values `SignalsOptInRBF` and `IsRBFOptIn`, alternatively you can return a new field (something like https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/16490).",
